description: {"blocks":[{"key":"19jr1","text":"Here we describe the method conducted to estimate (i) number of TH+ neurons in the substantia nigra pars compacta by taking advantage of a dedicated algorithm (Aiforia) and (ii) optical density of TH innervation in the putamen nucleus.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"95efj","text":"These two levels of analysis are required to properly estimate the potential damage of the nigrostriatal system in non-human primates, bot at origin (substantia nigra pars compacta) as well as at destination (putamen nucleus).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
ethics_statement: {"blocks":[{"key":"ep48b","text":"Animal handling was conducted in accordance to the European Council Directive 2010/63/UE as well as in full keeping with the Spanish legislation (RD53/2013). The experimental design was approved by the Ethical Committee for Animal Testing of the University of Navarra (ref: CEEA095/21) as well as by the Department of Animal Welfare of the Government of Navarra (ref: 222E/2021).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
